--- !u!114 &66074548
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 66074542}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0417832f9e1b60744bffb509fbfe905e, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::PrologueScreen
  paragraphs:
  - '<align="center">The Rightful King of <Capital> lead a peaceful reign for Many
    Years.



    Speakings of religious cults became more and more frequent, and
    rumour among them asserted that peace among the kingdoms was only a temporary
    state. In the shadows of the cities, more and more skeptics had been shown "Unrefutable
    Evidence" of the fall of Man, brought upon by the "Corrupted" King.



    The
    King and his intelligence viewed the rumours of this cult as harmless. The King
    was a worshipper of The Moon, and more and more evidence was showing the roots
    of the Doomsday Cult originated from the very leaders of the Temple of the Moon.



    To
    curb tensions and put rumours to rest, The King held a Public Forum, during which
    he asserted innocence, and announced his Pilgramage to The Temple of The Moon.
    His Pilgramage would include all leaders of the Government and the Military,
    and he vowed to his people that he would only continue his reign with The Blessing
    of the Temple of The Moon Priestesses, and The Moon Herself.'
  - "<align=\"center\">But as the sun rose over the city on the Dawn of The Pilgramage,
    Chaos erupted in the streets.\r\n\r\nFanatics of the Cult amassed in force. Their
    number were too overwhelming for the King's Guard to quell. As they ran through
    the streets, weapons drawn, the Fanatics spread the New Message of the Cult.\r\n\r\n\"The
    Moon herself has lead her people astray. Her Priestesses pleaded for humanity,
    but The Moon only left them in Shadows. Only while she is Shadowed by the World
    from the Light do we see her true form.\" \r\n\r\n<b><i>The Harbinger of Eternal
    Dark</i></b>\r\n\r\n\"Let it be known from this day, We are the People of the
    Light. The King has blinded us from this truth, as he is nothing but a Harbinger's
    Pawn\"\r\n\r\nThe Cultist Movement had grown too large, and repelling the uprising
    was impossible.\r\n\r\nThe King was captured, and in his final concious moments
    was forced to watch Cultists slit the throats of his Family, his Advisors, his
    Leaders..."
  - '<align="center">Days before the Uprising, as you walked the streets, a psychotic
    fanatic hounded you over the end of days.


    As you rolled your eyes, the
    fanatic lept at you, and in an act of self-defense, you drew your blade.


    Screams
    echoed as the fanatic lay lifeless in a pool of his own blood before you, and
    before you could explain yourself, you were in chains being taken to Prison to
    await Trial.


    Days passed, with no words from the guards of your fate, until
    one day, you woke up to a strange silence.


    No Guards bickering,


    No
    Guards screaming,


    No Guards Laughing,


    <b>No Guards</b>


    As this
    reality dawns on you, The Iron Gates holding you prisoner begin to slowly rise...'
  nextSceneName: Prison
  paragraphText: {fileID: 269593498}
  continueButton: {fileID: 1879238151}
  continueButtonText: {fileID: 158823640}
  canvasGroup: {fileID: 66074543}
  fadeInDuration: 1
  fadeOutDuration: 0.6
